int b { 9 };
int& r { a };
r = b;
```

The following program is supposed to print `100`, but it does not compile. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    int& r { 100 };
    std::cout << r << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

void addTen(int& n)
{
    n = n + 10;
}

int main()
{
    int val { 7 };
    addTen(val);
    std::cout << val << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```
